SLIDING WINDOW:-

A technique to process subarrays / substrings efficiently by maintaining a window over the data.

Instead of recalculating again and again,
ðŸ‘‰ reuse previous work.

brute force=> O(n*k)
sliding window=> O(n)   ->> it is O(n) because each element enters windows once and leaves windows once


* TYPES OF SLIDING WINDOW:-
1) fixed size window
2)variable size window

code:-(fixed sized window)

int maxSumSubarray(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
    int windowSum = 0, maxSum = INT_MIN;

    for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {
        windowSum += nums[i];

        if (i >= k - 1) {
            maxSum = max(maxSum, windowSum);
            windowSum -= nums[i - (k - 1)];
        }
    }
    return maxSum;
}


code:-(variable size window):-(general template):-

int left = 0;
for (int right = 0; right < n; right++) {

    // 1ï¸âƒ£ expand window
    add(nums[right]);

    // 2ï¸âƒ£ shrink until valid
    while (window is invalid) {
        remove(nums[left]);
        left++;
    }

    // 3ï¸âƒ£ update answer
    answer = max(answer, right - left + 1);
}

